{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"15e20d77-3d89-4fd9-81b8-5aa2fbbb220b","content":"The project doesn't exist yet, so I'll give you the configuration guidance directly.\n\nTo publish a C# console app as a **dotnet tool** on NuGet.org, add these properties to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server over stdio</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nKey points:\n\n1. **`PackAsTool`** — marks it as a dotnet tool.\n2. **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users will run (e.g. `my-mcp-server`).\n3. **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — tools must be console apps.\n\n### Pack & Publish\n\n```bash\ndotnet pack -c Release\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_NUGET_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### User install\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\nIf you want to include a `README.md` in the package, add an `<ItemGroup>` entry:\n\n```xml\n<ItemGroup>\n  <None Include=\"README.md\" Pack=\"true\" PackagePath=\"/\" />\n</ItemGroup>\n```\n\nThat's the minimum configuration needed. Want me to scaffold the project or apply these changes to an existing `.csproj`?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"10606790-25eb-401d-b24b-dc264a7dfbbb","outputTokens":522},"id":"fc2a0705-6f01-4cc5-a8b1-253645a8687a","timestamp":"2026-04-05T00:48:54.779Z","parentId":"26a56278-2616-4fa4-849c-779e2b7acc03"}
